</P>
<P>
   BUDGET-BATTLE (Washington) _ The annual fight over the federal
budget is about to get under way. Once again, the numbers-crunchers
will predict larger than expected surpluses, and Congress and the
White House will grapple with how to use it: to cut taxes, to
increase spending or to pay back the national debt. The arguments
are familiar, but with an election looming, the outcome could be
different. By William K. Stevens.
</P>
