   WWII-REFUGEES (Washington) _ The story of European Jews who
spent years in displaced persons camps after World War II is one of
the little known chapters of the Holocaust era. It was the subject
this weekend of a three-day conference and reunion in Washington.
</P>
<P>
   MONUMENT-SCAFFOLDING (Washington) _ One of the most anticipated
changes to the capital in the upcoming year is the new unveiling of
the restored Washington Monument, which has been wrapped in
scaffolding for over a year. But so many people love the
scaffolding itself that Target, the discount store, is planning to
buy it and put it up somewhere in Minnesota. By Francis X. Clines.
</P>
