<HEADLINE>
TREASURY AUCTION IS DELAYED BY HOLIDAY 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Because of the observance of Martin Luther King's birthday on
Monday, the Treasury will conduct its weekly auction of three- and
six-month bills on Tuesday. There are no other auctions scheduled
for the week.
</P>
<P>
   By the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 5.24 percent
and that of the six-month bill was 5.42 percent.
</P>
