<SLUG> BC-AKAMAI-OFFICE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AKAMAI TO OPEN CALIFORNIA OFFICE 
</HEADLINE>
  (ms) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Akamai Technologies, which had one of last year's hottest
Internet stock offerings, has expanded beyond its base in
Cambridge, Mass., to open an office in Silicon Valley.
</P>
<P>
   The company provides services that help Web sites perform more
efficiently by directing traffic to the least congested parts of a
network. Web sites that use Akamai's services included ones
operated by Walt Disney, Lycos and The New York Times Co.
</P>
<P>
   Akamai is opening the new office in San Mateo, Calif., partly
because some of its biggest accounts, like Apple Computer and
Yahoo, are nearby. But another goal is to tap the highly trained
labor pool of Silicon Valley, where workers are most likely to have
just the right combination of skills and training the company needs
_ even if they are also more likely to be infected by stock-option
fever than people in the East.
</P>
<P>
   Paul Sagan, Akamai's president, said that the company had hired
more than 25 new engineers in Silicon Valley.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's harder here in the Valley; they read the options letter
in much more detail,'' Sagan said. ``But you get some really
experienced and Internet-savvy people.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
