   BYE-BYE-BARNS (Washington, Iowa) _ Long the epitome of agrarian
life, old wood barns are vanishing from the American countryside.
They are being replaced by metal storage buildings, which are
cheaper and bigger, if short on charm. Experts on farm life say
more than half of the nation's wood barns have already been lost.
In Iowa alone, some 1,000 old barns disappear each year. By Dirk
Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
