<HEADLINE>
RAMS QB SHINES IN THE PLAYOFF SPOTLIGHT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. LOUIS _ Much of the pre-game doubt about the St. Louis Rams
surrounded quarterback Kurt Warner.
</P>
<P>
   Sure, he threw 41 touchdowns passes in the regular season and
won league MVP honors after being handed the starting quarterback
job after Trent Green suffered a season-ending injury in the
preseason.
</P>
<P>
   But this was the playoffs, the place where legends are made.
</P>
<P>
   Warner, an undrafted free-agent who spent time after college
stocking shelves at a grocery store in Iowa, had never seen a stage
this big.
</P>
<P>
   It is safe to say that the playoffs have seen few guys like
Warner. Warner completed 27 of 33 passes for 391 yards and five
touchdowns to five receivers in leading the Rams to a 49-37 victory
against the Minnesota Vikings in the NFC divisional playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   His completion percentage of 81.8 ranks as the third highest in
playoff history. His quarterback rating of 142.9 was eighth highest
in playoff history. Only two quarterbacks have thrown more than
five touchdowns in a playoff game. . The three combined for 15
receptions for 247 yards, including a 77-yard touchdown catch by
Bruce.
</P>
<P>
   Having running back Marshall Faulk helps as well. Faulk, who led
the team in receptions during regular season, caught five passes
for 80 yards, including a 41-yard touchdown in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
   However, the formerly unknown Warner is the man who makes the
Rams go.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's all Kurt,'' Hakim said. ``He is a great quarterback. He
sees his reads and makes the right connection.''
</P>
<P>
   Vikings coach Dennis Green, who said he voted for Warner as the
league MVP, is even more of a believer now.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a very good player,'' Green said. ``He made a lot of big
plays.''
</P>
<P>
   Actually Warner has been doing that since his days with the Iowa
Barnstormers when he led them to back-to-back Arena Bowl
appearances in 1996 and 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Warner is drawing on those Arena Bowl experiences for motivation
in the Rams' playoff run.
</P>
<P>
   ``I lost those two, and I don't want to lose any more,'' Warner
said.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
