the White House would help bring it to a speedy conclusion. (Keith
Meyers/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) DES MOINES, Iowa -- IOWA-GORE-LABOR -- Theresa Malin,
the Communication Workers of America, left, and Donna Mollis, the
American Federation of Teachers, both union members from
Washington, D.C., working the phone banks at the Iowa Federation of
Labor's headquarters in Des Moines. Notwithstanding labor's dismay
at the Clinton administration's trade policies, Iowa's union
movement has gone into overdrive in the past two weeks in an
attempt to give Gore a convincing caucus victory. (Rodney White/The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) HIGHLAND PARK, Ill. -- Jan. 16, 2000 --
5THGRADE-PROPHECY-REUNION-2 -- Carl Berg's 1983 fifth-grade
students from Sherwood Elementary in Highland Park. Seventeen years
ago, Berg asked the 27 students in his fifth-grade class, ages 10
and 11, to write essays imagining their lives and jobs, and those
of their classmates, in the year 2000. They also made a promise:
that when Berg called at the turn of the century to take
attendance, they would make every effort to avoid being marked
absent by their teacher, who would be 48, at a class reunion. (Todd
Buchanan/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
