   ECOMMERCE-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sorting out the growing number of
online cosmetics retailers. What are the various approaches, and
how do any of them hope to distinguish themselves? By Bod Tedeschi.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo [NYT4) has been sent to NYT photo clients.)
</P>
<P>
   AOL-DOMINATE (Undated) _ America Online is a strange hybrid,
combining content and connectivity in a manner unlike almost any
other Internet company. And the fact that it has come not only to
dominate the Internet but to personify it sends a strong signal to
its competitors, which include portal sites on the World Wide Web
like Yahoo and Lycos, as well as hundreds of Internet service
providers large and small. The message is this: find a way to
co-exist with this behemoth. By Katie Hafner.
</P>
<P>
   DOMAIN-DISPUTES (Washington) _ The World Wrestling Federation
has won back rights to the use of its name in cyberspace, in the
first case testing the new international forum for resolving
disputes over Internet domain names. By Jeri Clausing.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-MISSTEPS-MEDIA (Undated) _ A survivor of a
media-Internet merger from the pre-historic Internet era _ 1993 _
recalls the difficulties of trying to assemble an online service
backed by MCI, Rupert Murdoch's News Corp. and what was then a
leading Internet-access service, Delphi Internet. While some of the
missteps were part of the industry's generally stumbling search of
a media model, other lessons may still hold relevance for AOL Time
Warner. By Lisa Napoli.
</P>
